# Canon & World Rules

**Canonical source:** `Universe/canon_and_world_rules.md`

Reference this document before generating or editing any chapter content. It is a strict consistency layer — not narrative content.

## Authority

- This file overrides contradictory earlier draft descriptions
- Deviations require explicit in-story justification (prototype, malfunction, historical artifact, unknown technology)

## Fleet vessel class system (summary)

Combat hierarchy (smallest → largest): **Fighters → Ion Fighters → Corvettes → Frigates → Cruisers → Heavy Cruisers → Battleships → Dreadnaughts → Titans → Leviathans**, plus **Fleet Carriers** (battleship-sized, fighter deployment).

| Class | Primary weapon | Key role |
|-------|----------------|----------|
| Fighters | Lasers | Dogfighting, escort |
| Ion Fighters | Ion cannons | Anti-battleship; swarms vs titans/leviathans |
| Corvettes | Lasers | Anti-frigate, fast intercept |
| Frigates | Missiles | Anti-cruiser harassment, screening |
| Cruisers | Plasma | Anti-battleship; first shield class |
| Heavy Cruisers | Plasma (enhanced) | Anti-battleship/dreadnaught |
| Battleships | Ion | Anti-dreadnaught/titan; weak vs fighters alone |
| Dreadnaughts | Photon | Fortress defense; anti-frigate/fighter swarms |
| Titans | Disruptors | Anti-capital dominance |
| Leviathans | Photon | Strategic fleet annihilation |
| Fleet Carriers | Defensive only | ~400 fighters, air superiority |

## Tactical rules

- Use class roles consistently in battle descriptions
- Outcomes depend on role advantage, composition, and positioning — not size alone
- Do not blur class roles unless vessel is experimental or damaged

